  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-6 clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed: 12 are formally assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels; 1 factor (Equivalency of input parameters) is designated not-applicable with a detailed, borderline-call rationale documenting why the factor does not apply to this specific COU configuration. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points. Decision: Accepted.",
