      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed using ASME V&V 20 validation metric. Validation uncertainty Uval computed from experimental measurement uncertainty, numerical uncertainty, and input uncertainty. E/Uval < 1.0 at all 5 operating points for NIH, confirming predictions are within the validation uncertainty band. Velocity field comparison (PIV) also within Uval. Achieved level 5 exceeds required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is identical between the validation study and the COU. Hemolysis power-law model parameters (α = 3.62 × 10⁻⁷, β = 2.416, γ = 0.785) are the same in both contexts. No surrogate QoI substitution is performed. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope. Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity, density) match COU within documented uncertainty bounds. Geometric fidelity confirmed via coordinate measurement machine (CMM) comparison of physical test article to CAD nominal."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (all < 10⁻⁶) and QoI stabilization (NIH change < 0.05% over final 500 iterations). Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic verification. Solver error contribution to total uncertainty budget < 0.3% of NIH. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent CFD analyst with >10 years blood pump simulation experience. Boundary condition application, turbulence model selection (SST k-ω), and hemolysis model implementation verified against published Morrison et al. (2022) protocol. Simulation log files and setup files archived under version control. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "Turbulence model (SST k-ω) selected based on published benchmark studies demonstrating superior performance for rotating machinery hemolysis prediction. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients re-calibrated by Taskin et al.) is the accepted standard for this device class. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison with Eulerian vs. Lagrangian hemolysis tracking; difference < 12% NIH, included in UQ budget. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profiles, rotational speed) assigned probability distributions based on experimental characterization data. Monte Carlo analysis (N = 10,000 samples, Latin hypercube sampling) propagates input uncertainty to NIH predictions. 95th-percentile NIH bounds confirmed below clinical threshold at all 5 operating points. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5-criteria",
      "rationale": "In vitro hemolysis measurements performed on N = 5 independent test samples (pump units) per ASTM F1841 protocol. Inter-sample variability (CV < 8%) documented and incorporated into experimental uncertainty estimate. Sample traceability to lot numbers and hematocrit measurements confirmed. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-input-params-na-justification",
      "rationale": "This factor addresses the equivalency of model input parameters between a validation case and a separate, distinct COU case — specifically the scenario where validation is performed on a surrogate or predicate device and results are extrapolated to the COU device. In the present assessment, the validation activities were conducted on the identical device geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump, serial number GCP-2023-001 through GCP-2023-005) under the identical operating conditions that constitute the COU. There is no surrogate-to-COU extrapolation step; the validation case IS the COU case. Applying the Equivalency of Input Parameters factor in this context would require assessing the equivalency of inputs between a case and itself, which is a degenerate and uninformative exercise. This borderline determination was reviewed by the credibility assessment team and the independent reviewer (Dr. A. Marsden, Stanford Cardiovascular Biomechanics Lab) on 2026-03-14. The team acknowledges that this call is borderline: if the Monte Carlo input distributions were defined using data from a different pump unit population than the validation test articles, an equivalency assessment would be warranted. However, the input distributions were derived from the same five test articles used in validation, and all boundary conditions are specified from the same measurement campaign. The not-applicable designation is therefore justified under ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 5.3.2, which permits factor scoping when the factor's underlying concern is structurally absent from the assessment context. This determination is documented in Assessment Review Record ARR-2026-003 and is not used to avoid any credibility burden — all other 12 factors are fully assessed."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 (VAD hemolysis prediction, MRL 5) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 12 formally assessed credibility factors achieve levels meeting or exceeding required levels at MRL 5, with Output Comparison exceeding required level by one gradation (achieved 5 vs. required 4). (2) The one not-applicable factor (Equivalency of Input Parameters) carries a detailed, peer-reviewed rationale documented in ARR-2026-003, establishing that the factor's underlying concern — surrogate-to-COU extrapolation — is structurally absent because validation and COU share identical geometry, operating conditions, and input characterization data. (3) Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (N = 10,000) confirms that the 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L at all five COU operating points, with the most conservative operating point yielding a 95th-percentile NIH of 0.0073 g/100 L (27% margin to threshold). (4) The validation metric E/Uval < 1.0 at all operating points confirms that model predictions are consistent with experimental measurements within combined uncertainty. (5) Independent review by Dr. A. Marsden confirmed all factor assessments and the not-applicable designation. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the Class III VAD device, subject to the condition that any change in device geometry, operating envelope, or hemolysis model coefficients triggers reassessment of all affected factors.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
